```markdown
# Using GitHub Project (Kanban) for the Team

Suggested columns
- Backlog (new issues)
- To do (planned for next sprint)
- In progress (active work; link branch/PR)
- In review (PR open)
- Done (merged/deployed)

How to use
- Add each task as an issue and link it to the project.
- Move issue cards as their state changes.
- Reference issue numbers in commits and PRs: fixes #12

Suggested automation
- Connect PRs to move cards automatically (GitHub Projects automation).
- Use labels: bug, feature, docs, high-priority.
```
